title: Design one of Caliche's Frozen Custard's product labels called "DESERT ICE" !
description:
Hello! We are Caliche's Frozen Custard, a quick service restaurant with over 25 years of experience serving southern New Mexico with the tastiest treats and hot dogs in the state! We are a local staple in our communities and work tremendously hard to make sure our restaurants stay memorable and unique. We invest a lot of our time and resources into our brand, especially here through our 99designs account.
In this particular project, we are wanting to update one of our logos of a seasonal summertime product called, DESERT ICE. This product is basically our take on Italian Ice or Water Ice. With our different variations of logos that we've had, we have always tried to play around with the hot and cold theme with the logo. We have had a difficult time getting the logo to look like we want. What we really like about the original logo is how the logo is reads from left to right (landscape) rather than stacked. We also like how the word ICE is designed with snow on under the letters. As you can see, with the word DESERT, we are trying to go for a hot or desert theme. This is where we have failed in the past with designing this logo, the word never comes out how we like it, mostly because we don't like the way the desert is designed. We are really particular in making sure the desert is similar to the actual topography of New Mexico and not of Egypt or or Arizona.
In all honesty, we do not have any strong wishes to keep this going in the new version unless we see a design that really nails the desert theme. I would much rather focus on making sure the design compliments the rest of our brand including our main logo. Our brand colors are: Raspberry (dark pink), Blue Berry (blue), and Strawberry (light pink), you can see our brand colors in the brief as well. We would like our desert ice to play with the hot and cold theme but also really compliment our logo if we choose to feature both logos on the same design.
We would also like to see a version with the slogan and without the slogan.
other_color_requirements: Play with warm and cold colors to achieve the hot and cold theme. Make sure we are complimenting the text and colors for our main brand logo.
other_notes:
What is provided in the brief is our original desert ice logo as well as our main brand logos in different versions.
You will also notice in the original logo design that we have a mascot. We would like to have this mascot also be redesigned to fit the logo that is created. Please make sure that the logo is not too youthful and looks close to the original logo that you see (keep the items that he is holding also in the new design). Thank you!
You can visit our website Caliches.com to look at more of our brand.

title: Design a modern logo for an established CA remodeling firm to appeal to millennials
description:
Gayler Design Build is a family-owned design-build remodeling firm committed to quality construction, innovative design, and long-lasting relationships built on integrity and straightforward communication. They ae an unrivalled, award-winning design and construction firm with 22 national and regional design awards. Founded in 1961, they are located in Danville, CA and serve the Tri-Valley and Lamorinda regions. With an enviable 20-year track record, Gayler has completed every project on time, and on budget. From completing whole house remodels, kitchen and bath renovations and additions, to finishing outdoor living spaces, Gayler has been successful at executing the job to each customer’s satisfaction, incorporating personal design customization into every project.
The company’s ideal clients are homeowners living in expensive neighborhoods within Contra Costa County. They typically are 30 to 55 years of age (Millennial and Gen X) and married with children who value efficiency and will pursue a working relationship with a trusted building contractor. They prefer having an active role in the design and construction process and place their trust in a contractor with a superior product or service history. They also demand digital communications and are willing to pay a premium price for quality construction.
These “Simple Life” homeowners have an affinity for outdoor activities. The head of household is between 35 and 54, have a high rate of ownership (89% nationally), have average home values between $200,000 and $500,000 nationally (local home value $1M+), and is the consumer group most likely to have 2-3 dogs, 2-3 cats, did remodel by self in last 12 months, and will travel an hour or more to shop favorite stores.
Behaviors
Gayler’s ideal clients have typically never built a home before or remodeled. If they have remodeled, they’ve done it themselves and only smaller DIY projects. When it comes to the dynamics of a large construction project, they fear the worst. They prefer to shop products and features first and have little patience for inefficient or poor service. Consequently, the more flexible you can be with products and selections and the more responsive you are in the design process, the better. Gayler clients are also very interested in being engaged throughout the process, placing their trust in brands with a superior product or service history, and they want partners that will help guide them to their big purchases.
As such, comfort is realized in Gayler’s reputation for high-end quality construction, and end-to-end customer service. They also value design innovation and working with a firm that encourages all creative ideas, questions, and collaboration (i.e., a responsive process).
Gayler’s ideal clients demand digital communications, including invoices and status reports, in almost real time. They seek digital tools to help manage their debt. As such, comfort is realized in Gayler’s thorough and detailed proposals and efficient tools (e.g., Buildertrend) to communicate openly with them throughout the project.
other_notes:
We are looking to create a modern, striking logo that is clean and crisp, professional, and also warm and friendly – not to come across like a stuffy law firm. Our hope is that we can create a logomark that cleverly speaks to residential remodeling design, without using an overused “tool” in the imagery. We are looking for a logo mark that uses the letter “G” and creatively creates a roof line or “home” image in the negative space or in the design elements somehow.
Gayler is part DESIGN Firm and part Construction Contractor. The team works collectively together to help people design and build their dream home. It’s important that the logo look beautifully, and creatively designed (representative of an architectural design firm or a designer) NOT a hard logo with hard edges that represents construction only.
